techmeme.title: Apple unveils M3 Ultra, built from two 3nm M3 Max chips, offering Thunderbolt 5, a new UltraFusion packaging architecture, 80-core GPU, and up to 512GB memory (Andrew E. Freedman/Tom's Hardware)
Apple updates the Mac Studio with an M4 Max for $1,999+ and an M3 Ultra for $3,999+, with up to 32 cores, including 24 performance cores, shipping from March 12 (Wes Davis/The Verge)
Apple updates the $999+ 13-inch and $1,199+ 15-inch MacBook Air with M4, with a 10-core CPU and 8-core GPU, and a new sky blue color option, shipping March 12 (Antonio G. Di Benedetto/The Verge)
The UK CMA clears Microsoft's $13B OpenAI investment in 2023, ending 14 months of uncertainty over the deal, but says "Microsoft did acquire material influence" (Upmanyu Trivedi/Bloomberg)
Digg founder Kevin Rose and Reddit founder Alexis Ohanian buy Digg for an undisclosed sum from Money Group, aiming to focus on "connection and humanity" online (Mike Isaac/New York Times)
